name: PixelFem #44 - Margaret Hamilton
description:
Margaret Hamilton, was a computer pioneer who had the critical task of landing astronauts on the moon for the first time on 20 July 1969 and returning them safely a few days later. The young computer programmer and working mother led the team that created the onboard flight software for the Apollo missions, including Apollo 11.

✺This work is part of PixelFems, an evolving project on the Tezos blockchain celebrating iconic women from the past and present✺
